This paper is related to wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically addresses the issue of energy consumption in sensor nodes, which is a common problem in wireless sensor networks. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under computer networks and security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.MA), as these fields often deal with optimizing network performance and energy efficiency. Additionally, the paper involves the use of clustering techniques, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
